WorldStage Newsonline– Livingtrust Mortgage Bank Plc has released its interim unaudited financial statements for half year ended 30th June 2022 with 58.83% jump in profit after tax to N489.620 million in half year from N308.257 million in H1 2021. Profit   after tax in the second quarter rose by 140.53% to N242.496 million from N100.819 million in Q2 2021. Gross earnings by the mortgage bank rose to N1.12 billion in H1 from N664.093 million in H1 2021 while the figure for the Q2 rose to N617.163 million from N251.790 million in Q2 2021.